spanGrp.span: But they are disappearing little by little;
the other people do not defend them.
siga-wa ka je të í ktëishe ĩã
Everything we do is of great value.
(hm) Jirö klabe wẽ-gẽ sa të je sigei tã'ĩ
Other people feel ashamed of speaking our language
Siga-wa sũãr/ siga-wa ũr-gẽ se ktö' shö
because people may laugh at them;
(_) Pe të se je ñẽtse-mĩ pe të (_) she-mĩ
People ask me why I speak like that.
Well, it is my language; it is the tongue I use to speak!
Ka yörö wö nã je döwã
but I understand what I say.
Yís wagi wö nã í dömĩwãũ jirö shá-je
Some people do not believe that there are so many things.
(_) Jirö klabe tsõ bi Ujarras të je ra maleska-wa ka të í kuge
We go by San Jose and other places
and then our relatives only want to speak like the whites,
ka klabe je se damãũ je ra sa sa yaiwa kta-gle rö (_) pe ye bö
Je ra se je ktö' ka she-ite
But today we are told that our language has great value
Je ra jiska <se ĩã í> yir-nã' se ktö' sigei tã'ĩ
and should not be given away.’
